1. Inventory & Stock Management
The backbone of any pharmacy system is knowing exactly what is on the shelves.

    Medicine Categorization: Organize products by type (Tablet, Syrup, Injection) or category (Antibiotics, Painkillers, Vitamins).

    Stock Tracking: Real-time updates of stock levels as sales occur.

    Expiration Date Alerts: A critical pharmacy feature that flags batches nearing their expiry date to prevent selling unsafe medication.

    Low-Stock Notifications: Automatic alerts when items fall below a specific "reorder level."

2. Sales & Point of Sale (POS)
This handles the customer-facing transactions.

    Transaction Processing: A simple interface to search for medicine, add to cart, and calculate totals/taxes.

    Receipt Generation: Automated digital or printable receipts for every sale.

    Discount Management: Apply senior citizen or PWD discounts as required by local regulations.

    Sales History: A searchable log of all past transactions for auditing purposes.

3. Appointment Management System
This is your "X-factor" feature, allowing customers to book services.

    Service Selection: Let users book appointments for vaccinations, blood pressure monitoring, or pharmacist consultations.

    Real-time Availability: A calendar view showing open time slots to prevent overbooking.

    Appointment Status: Track bookings through stages like Pending, Confirmed, Completed, or Cancelled.

4. User Roles & Security
Ensure the right people have the right access.

    Multi-Level Access: * Admin: Full access (reports, employee management, inventory).

    Pharmacist/Staff: Can process sales and manage appointments.

    Secure Authentication: Encrypted login system for all staff members.

    Activity Logs: A record of which user performed specific actions (e.g., who deleted a stock entry).

5. Reports & Analytics
Transforming data into insights for the business owner.

    Daily Sales Reports: Total revenue generated within a 24-hour period.

    Top-Selling Medicines: A list of the most popular products to help with restocking decisions.

    Appointment Trends: Reports on the busiest days or most requested services.
